description:
The Timberwolves ended the game on a 16-4 run to defeat the Lakers, 117-95. The Timberwolves were led by the 25 points and 9 rebounds and 3 three pointers from Jaden McDaniels, as Naz Reid (23 points) and Anthony Edwards (22 points, 9 assists) combined to add 45 points. The Timberwolves knocked down a Playoff franchise record 21 3PM in the win. The Lakers were led by Luka Dončić, who had 37 points and 8 rebounds and 5 three pointers. The Timberwolves lead the series 1-0.
